Kenya on Friday recorded 502 new cases of Covid-19 from a sample size of 3,503 tested in the last 24 hours. The positivity rate is now at 14.3 per cent. The Ministry of Health said from the cases 456 are Kenyans while 46 are foreigners. Of these, 261 are males and 241 females. "The youngest is a one-year-old while the oldest is 95 years old," Health CS Mutahi Kagwe said. The total confirmed positive cases are now at 331,539 and cumulative tests so far conducted are 3,738,841. "Today, 280 patients have recovered from the disease, all of them from the Home-Based and Isolation Care Program," he added. This pushes the total recoveries to 321,774 of whom 268,655 are from the Home-Based Care and Isolation program, while 53,119 are from various health facilities countrywide. No patient succumbed to the disease therefore the cumulative fatalities remain at 5,651. There are 99 patients currently admitted to the health facilities, while 3,513 are under the Home-Based Isolation and Care program. Two patients are in the Intensive Care Unit (ICU) on ventilator support, while 16 are in General Wards on supplemental oxygen. No patient is in the High Dependency Unit (HDU). As of Thursday, a total of 18,696,980 vaccines have been administered across the country. The total number of booster doses admitted so far is 438,391. The Government is working towards vaccinating a targeted population of 27,246,033.